WHEN PRESENT (?i)\b(login|authenticate|oauth|jwt)\b
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:(?i)\b(auth|login|token|session|credential)\b && MISSING:(?i)\b(readme|changelog|example|sample|docs?|license|copyright|third[-_ ]party)\b
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects common terms used in authentication functionalities, such as 'Login', 'authenticate', 'OAuth', and 'JWT', when used in likely function names or module references.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Authentication Modules.
